Utterances: do you know why you are here?
Those idiot cops brought me here. I don't need to be here but the front desk guy said that they have to check me out. Like I'm some sort of book in the history of atlases.
do you know why they brought you here?

Well, I was heading into the grocery store for some sushi when I sensed someone was following me -- there are these government agents that like to chase me, so I was like, crap crap crap crap. I had to check inside cars to see where they were. I guess I probably looked like a crazy person, running around and everything.
who do you think those people are?
I'm a leader. I'm a visionary. When I say, "Don't slip on that banana peel," I mean it.
what do you think those government agent would do to you? (Clarified to Who are the government agents?.)

I mean, what do you want to know? I just had a hunch they were in one of those cars, waiting to scoop me up and throw me in solitary. They know I'm enlightened and if my writings get out, boom, their secrets are overthrown. Not that I'm gonna let them stop me. (Clarified to who the government agents are.)
do you have history of anxiety?

I'm not anxious or paranoid or whatever. I mean, I just have a really really fine-tuned sense of, like, OK, now they're coming for me, the government agents, and I have to be on the look out, 'cause no way am I being snatched up, not a chance.
the people you saw are not government agent.
I don't need you to be my guidance counselor or anything . . .
do you have history of hallucinations?
Not that I know of. I don't know much about my birth parents or their family, though.
do you feel someone taking to you or see things which other people can not see? (No matching questions found.)
do you have hallucinations?
No way. I don't see junk that's not there or anything.
have you used any illicit drugs?
I guess cocaine is still illegal, right? That's the war on drugs for ya.
have you recently used any illicit drugs? (Clarified to Have you used illegal drugs recently?.)
I'm as sober as a kitchen sink right now. I haven't done anything for like, four days. I should really call my dealer. (Clarified to if I have used illegal drugs recently.)
how often do you sleep?

Come on, Professor Healthcare. You think I'm keeping track? Too much to do. Too much to see. Two plus two is . . . it's on the tip of my tongue, the glistening tip! No sleepy bye-bye for maybe four days now.
have you tried any things to fall asleep.
Thanks a million, but I'm all good, I promise!
it is important to sleep for proper body function and rest.
Thanks, but you don't need to worry about me.
do you have energy to do your everyday work? (No matching questions found.)
what is your current energy level?
Oh, man, I'm like, if a cheetah drank a coffee and then stepped on a wire. Not that cheetahs like coffee.
what is your current mood?
I am 100% letting the good times roll. Couldn't be better.
when did you started to feel you have energy and good mood? (Clarified to When did the symptoms begin?.)
I don't have symptoms, buddy. I was brought here against my will. I'm sure the cops think I'm sick, but as you'll find out, I'm as healthy as the wealthy. (Clarified to when my symptoms started.)
when did you started to feel energetic and happy?

I've had the jazz in my blood for a week, I'd say. It's been all trumpets and horn ever since. Gosh, I always knew it could be this way. Me, being the best version of myself. The world, parting its lip like a dang oyster for my consumption. What a life! Ain't it a song?
what other health conditions you have?

My health is fine, OK? Like, I'm not here because of my health. The cops brought me here for lord knows what, and my only major health thing has ever been my depression, but that's six feet under now, so we're good.
have you taken any medication for your depression? (Clarified to Did you take medication for depression?.)
I used to, yeah. (Clarified to if I took medication for my depression.)
have you been hospitalized before?
Not since, I wanna say 3 years ago . . . yeah. It's not a big deal. We're good.
do you have any medication and food allergies? (Clarified to Do you have medication allergies?.)

I don't have any, I don't think, though I haven't really had that many meds in my life. Maybe if you gave me, like, Zorpizol I would grow, you know -- Zorps everywhere. Zorp Zorp. Like, that's the sound of Zorps, they go, Zooooorp. (Clarified to if I have medication allergies.)
what is your mood throughout the day? (Clarified to Tell me about your current mood?.)

I'm a prospector taking in the view, that's what's up. I've been working on my poem like crazy and hanging out with my friends. Ain't gonna brag, but having some good sexy time, too. I am truly living the greatest guitar riff ever. Bow meow b-b-bow! (Clarified to to tell you about my current mood.)
how is your mood now? (Clarified to How are your mood and energy right now?.)
Amazing! I feel great! I'm bursting at the gills--is, is that what people say? Up, up to the gills? Step right up, boys and gills! (Clarified to how my mood and energy are right now.)
how is your typical mood?
You've got Option A and Option B. With A, we're talking about a bottomless rat hole. With B, we're talking good vibes that don't disappoint. I'll stick with B, thanks.
how is your typical mood levels?
You've got Option A and Option B. With A, we're talking about a bottomless rat hole. With B, we're talking good vibes that don't disappoint. I'll stick with B, thanks.
how is your typical energy levels?
Arg! Picture this: a ship on the sea. The waves go up and down. The ship bobs. What's normal if the ship's a'bob? You tell me. I've been high and I've been low.
how often does your mood changes?
I'm not keeping track or anything, but maybe a couple times a year? I don't know. This is a really nice room. I really like this room.
how long did your depression lasted?
I dunno, it was just a long time, OK? It's not a big deal. It was long, yes. I didn't, like, mark a calendar.
when were you diagnosed with depression?

We're dredging up this junk--well, I got diagnosed with depression like three years ago. Three little pigs. Wonder what happened to the third pig . . . I bet he got diagnosed, too. Squealer. It's like going fishing and pulling up an old boot.
have you seen psychiatrist?

The answer is yes, but I'm not a loon! There's nothing wrong with me. I saw a psychiatrist after a wee little suicide attempt. My parents flipped. I got hospitalized--worst time of my life. Let's talk about something else, okay?
did you felt better after your psychiatrist visit?
That's super cool of you, thanks!
have you thought of killing yourself?
Yeah . . . yeah, when I get really depressed. But that's completely in the past, I'm just -- I -- I feel really like it's completely done, and I'm just smooth sailing here on out.
do you take any home medications?
I'm not on anything these days. Stopped those antidepressants a while back. Zombie pills, honestly. Stuff is necrotic.
what your the side effects you felt after taking medication? (Clarified to What kind of side effects have you experienced from medications?.)
Dude, just drop it, OK? It doesn't matter. Jeez Louise. (Clarified to what medication side effects I have experienced.)
it is important to know the side effect of medication so that you won't have that effects again.
I'm not really taking any advice right now, but thanks anyway!
have you been prescribed any medication?

I've only ever been on antidepressants, and not anymore. That stuff dulls your vibes. Y'all should be careful about giving it out too much. You're gonna have a Shadowville full of zombies with no zookeeper. Meow.
what other medication are you being prescribed?
I've only ever taken antidepressants.
do you know why those medication are given to you? (No matching questions found.)
when was the medication prescribed to you? (Clarified to When was the last time you took any medications?.)
Ha! Antidepressants I took, like, three years ago. I don't remember the exact date. Left my almanac at home. (Clarified to when I last took medication.)
you said you have attempted suicide i need to follow up on that.
Hey, I appreciate the good vibes.
how many times have to tried to attempt suicide? (Clarified to How many times have you attempted suicide?.)
One time. That was enough. (Clarified to how many times I have attempted suicide.)
do you remember why you tried to kill yourself? (Clarified to What were your reasons for your suicide attempt?.)
I don't want to talk about it, OK? I don't want to talk about it. It was 3 years ago. Let it go. (Clarified to what my reasons were for my suicide attempt.)
it is important to talk about so that we know you are not feeling to kill yourself again.
You can save the words of wisdom for somebody who needs 'em.
do you want to be dead?
No! Really, that's not me. That's not -- it gets like -- obviously, when you're depressed, you think like that, sure. But that's not me anymore, so whatever. I'm not worried about it.
so do you feel that other people would be better off without you? (Clarified to Do you ever think other people would be better off without you?.)
. . . No. Do I feel like that? No. That's all I care to say. No. (Clarified to if I ever think other people would be better off without me.)
do you have any plans to kill yourself?
Aw, come on, bud, do I seem like the type? I haven't even considered planning that sort of thing since maybe 3 years ago, and that's when I actually went through it.
do you try to harm yourself?
I really don't want to talk about it. You're being a bummer, honestly. I was in a good mood before we started talking about this.
have to tried to harm yourself without trying to die?
No, not at all. Such a bummer question. I only really got like that during my one suicide attempt. One as in done.
do you have homicidal urges?
. . . Wow, what a lovely question. No, I don't. I can't believe you would even ask that.
we have to ask to all the people who have suicidal thought.
Thanks. You and me, we've got a real connection.
what is mental health to you? (Clarified to How do you feel about your mental health?.)

My brain is superb, honestly. It's frickin' cotton candy and sports car up there. Don't worry about me. Like, yeah, I was depressed before, if that's what you're asking. But that's as dead as a doornail, hangnail, all the nails. (Clarified to how I feel about my mental health.)
have you had any recent change in mood or energy? (Clarified to Has your mood changed lately?.)

Yeah, definitely. A week ago, it was like, suddenly like--you know how it feels when you slam the pedal down and there's this, like, weightless moment when the car's about to pick up? The proverbial sweet spot before going hyper-speed. Yeah. I finally feel like myself. (Clarified to if I have had changes in my mood.)
have other notice about your mood change or energy shift?
Who knows what other people notice? Personally, I notice everything, but you can't expect every chump on the street to be enlightened.
how often do you feel angry?
If somebody's threatening my vibes, I'm gonna argue. That's all it is. I'm having an amazing time and I just want everybody to be on my level.
how many hours do you sleep?
I usually only need a couple hours. These past four days? I haven't slept a wink. Not even tired. I'm the frickin' man, I know.
have you notice any change in speed of moving or speaking?
I mean, nah, I'm just a super quick guy in general. I like to get things done and keep 'em moving. Talk fast, walk fast, all that. What can I say, some horses weren't meant for carriages.
do you have any racing thoughts?
Like a greyhound. Hyah! Hyah! But it works out great, because I'm working on this massive poem that's all about--well, it's gonna blow people's minds.
what activities interests you?

Well, my main thing is this epic poem I've been writing for a while. It's -- you don't even KNOW how epic. And I've been super productive lately . . . like this week I've started maybe 45 chapters. Settin' myself up for later. I mean, gimme a break -- who's better than me?
do you have any activities that gives pleasure to you? (No matching questions found.)
do you have any activities that gives pleasure? (No matching questions found.)
what activities gives you pleasures?

I've always been super interested in literature, like making meaning of the world we live in. Kinda of bleeds into my philosophical meanderings you know. The epic poem I'm working on is super exciting, like world-changing kind of stuff. Forget your chicken scratch is all I'm saying.
do you have interest in typical activities?

Heck yeah, my life is the best. There's joy everywhere. There's joy in this hospital room, not that you would know much about that. Yeah, you really just gotta keep an eye out for it, my friend. Just squint and you'll see it.
are you sexually active?
That's an understatement. I'm kinda savage in that department. It's where I shine. This week may be the most carnal I've ever been. I'm slayin'.
what sexual activities are you engaged in?
It's just intense, you know? We're kinda like, boom boom boom boom! I don't--I, I don't know how else to describe it. It's just like waka waka waka ka-blam.
what do you do in most of your time?

I've always been super interested in literature, like making meaning of the world we live in. Kinda of bleeds into my philosophical meanderings you know. The epic poem I'm working on is super exciting, like world-changing kind of stuff. Forget your chicken scratch is all I'm saying.
what are your spending habits?
Well, I'm spending on the stuff that matters. I'm talking about a little cocaine here, some rare books there. I help my friends out however I can because you know? I'm a giver.
do you have enough money to give food? (Clarified to Can you afford food?.)

I can afford whatever I need, honest! My parents throw me a bone now and then. Honestly, though, I don't need in the way of food and essentials, all that. I'm more into buying, like, stellar cocaine and sick rare books from olden times. And giving my friends cash, I love that. I'm a really really good person, I just naturally love doing it! (Clarified to if we can afford food.)
what is your occupation?
I'm in between jobs right now. Actually, I'm more in between not having a job and not having a job.
what do you do for living?

My proverbial living is this witch's brew of the finest poetry and a whole lotta hang-time with my best pals. Shout out to you, Ellen! Jamie! Tom! The past week's been the best week of my life! Thanks to Mom and Dad for giving me some dough, too. Let's keep it up, everybody.
do you like to work?
I'm in between jobs right now. Actually, I'm more in between not having a job and not having a job.
did you have any legal troubles?
Not at all! I'm the patron saint of innocence! Hah. No, really though, I've never gotten so much as a ticket.
what occupation do you like most? (Clarified to What was your occupation?.)

In the past--I worked at a pizza place once. Another time my dad's friend let me work at his office. I put Christmas trees on people's cars. I worked at an insurance office for like two weeks one time. (Clarified to what my job was.)
do you drink alcohol?
Yeah, like everyone on earth. There's nothing unnatural about drinking potato juice. That's what it is, you know.
how often do you drink alcohol or use drugs?

Not often -- 2 or 3 times a week, I guess. It's more of a party vibe than anything. I drink more when I'm down, but I'm not down anymore! It's all loose goose these days. I'm not, like, waking up with the hair of the dog. That's like, no hair and no dogs for me, thank you.
how often do you use drugs?
I'm no math whiz, pop, bang!--but I probably do a couple lines a couple times a week.
drinking and drug use can have negative effect on your health when you already have history of depression.
Whatever. I literally could NOT be any better.
what makes you think that you are better taking drugs and alcohol.
Save your tears for the whales! I'm doing awesome.
how do you travel to places? (Clarified to Do you use your car to get around?.)
Sure, I've got a sweet ride. That thing purrs like a kitten. (Clarified to if I use my car to get around.)
how often do you eat?
Once or twice a day? This week just once-ish. I'm never really that hungry, but this week especially my stomach is a no-fly-zone.
have you tried eating food you like.
I don't need you to be my guidance counselor or anything . . .
have you tried drinking water before or between meals.
Hey, I appreciate the good vibes.
how much water do you drink in a day?

Uh, I don't keep track, I'm not a marine biologist. What am I, a marine biologist? Hah. Just, like, writing down how much water I drink. That's -- that's hilarious. Like some loser with too many water bottles. Anyway, I dunno. A glass here or there, probably once a day-ish.
do you dink coffee? (No matching questions found.)
do you like to drink coffee?
Do I look like a guy who needs caffeine? This is au naturale, baby. I don't need no crushed up bean juice that tastes like tree poop.
what is education history? (Clarified to What is the highest level of education you have?.)
I did a year in college a while back. (Clarified to how much education I have.)
do you have access to healthcare?
Yeah, I'm on my parents' insurance. It's such a crock, though, these insurance goons and the Super Pharm Outlet Malls of America . . .
do you live alone or with family?
I'm a lone bird. I just sleep in my car, mostly. My friends let me couch surf, too.
do you spend time with your family? (Clarified to How often do you see your family?.)

Not that often, since they kicked me out. Them thinking I'm a worthless junkie who needs rehab doesn't exactly make for pleasantries. But who needs 'em, honestly. Like, I have the best friends in the world. Why would I need some, like, backwards squares who haven't even set foot in a dive bar? (Clarified to how often I see my family.)
do you have history of abuse?
Dang, are you serious?! No, not at all. Dang, what a wet blanket question. No, that's never happened to me. Dang. Screwin' up the vibes.
does your family has history of mental illness?
No . . . I couldn't tell you anything about my birth parents, but my real parents are pretty sane. They're kinda, like, massive normies. Wouldn't know art if it hit 'em in the balls.
do you have headache?
My head feels great! I'm having the time of my life.
do you have any history of heart problems?
Hey, man. Look in my pockets if you want to. No history of heart problems there.
do you have skin problems?
Problems? With my skin? Which exhibits such astounding beauty that moths are attracted to me in the night, circling and circling? Yeah, right.
how often do you have bowel movement?
I'm on the poop deck every three days or so, dropping a deuce in the deep blue sea.
is there any change in your ability to concentration? (Clarified to Have you had any changes in concentration?.)

Oh, I've been laser-focused lately. On my poetry, that is. On my friends' projects. I told you we're thinking about making this community art center? It would be so sick. We'll see. It's all in the works. (Clarified to if I have had changes in concentration.)
all the question that i ask you is to provide you with better care.
Thanks. You and me, we've got a real connection.
is there anything else that you would like to share with me?
Thanks a million, but I'm all good, I promise!
you should try some relaxation techniques and meditating which can help you calm down.
